The men jump up.

00:54:52.570 --> 00:54:54.610
And they shift over
one station.

00:54:54.610 --> 00:54:57.160
And then what happens is, for
each time you meet a person,

00:54:57.160 --> 00:54:59.080
you fill out a card that says
yes or no I'd be willing to

00:54:59.080 --> 00:55:00.260
have a date with the person.

00:55:00.260 --> 00:55:03.930
And if you have two yeses from
the man and the woman, the

00:55:03.930 --> 00:55:07.020
speed dating organizer exchanges
the information so

00:55:07.020 --> 00:55:08.520
they can make direct contact.

00:55:08.520 --> 00:55:09.970
Does that sound OK?

00:55:09.970 --> 00:55:13.050
And men make more
yes responses.

00:55:13.050 --> 00:55:16.040
And it turns out, it doesn't
have to be this way, but

00:55:16.040 --> 00:55:19.480
almost, from my reading, that
almost every speed dating

00:55:19.480 --> 00:55:22.460
thing has the men rotating
around and the women sitting

00:55:22.460 --> 00:55:24.540
there waiting for the men
to rotate around.

00:55:24.540 --> 00:55:26.810
So let's just ask
this question.

00:55:26.810 --> 00:55:29.770
What happens if the women
rotate, which

00:55:29.770 --> 00:55:30.770
almost never happens?

00:55:30.770 --> 00:55:32.430
But they did this
experimentally.

00:55:32.430 --> 00:55:36.040
They said for half of the speed
dating sessions the men

00:55:36.040 --> 00:55:37.310
will be sitting at the table.

00:55:37.310 --> 00:55:39.380
And the women will stand up and
move a chair over every

00:55:39.380 --> 00:55:39.810
four minutes.

00:55:39.810 --> 00:55:40.570
The bell rings.

00:55:40.570 --> 00:55:43.280
So the women are moving
and rotating.

00:55:43.280 --> 00:55:45.900
And here's the results.

00:55:45.900 --> 00:55:48.880
Basically, what's showing on
the left are when the men

00:55:48.880 --> 00:55:51.250
rotate, the standard
condition.

00:55:51.250 --> 00:55:52.690
First, it's romantic desire.

00:55:52.690 --> 00:55:55.640
Men feel more romantic desire,
on average, for the partner

00:55:55.640 --> 00:55:56.580
they sit with.

00:55:56.580 --> 00:55:59.680
They feel that more chemistry
is happening with the person

00:55:59.680 --> 00:56:00.490
they sit with.

00:56:00.490 --> 00:56:07.620
And on the bottom left corner,
they also are more likely to

00:56:07.620 --> 00:56:11.530
give a yes response, I would
like a date with this person.

00:56:11.530 --> 00:56:14.590
But reverse the roles, have the
women rotating, and look

00:56:14.590 --> 00:56:16.330
at these bars.

00:56:16.330 --> 00:56:18.570
There's no difference at all.

00:56:18.570 --> 00:56:22.220
You completely wipe out the
male female difference and

00:56:22.220 --> 00:56:26.140
self-reported romantic desire
per person, self-reported

00:56:26.140 --> 00:56:28.790
chemistry they think is
happening, and the yes no

00:56:28.790 --> 00:56:30.020
responses that I would
have a date.

00:56:30.020 --> 00:56:33.750
You completely eliminate it when
the women are rotating.

00:56:33.750 --> 00:56:35.440
It's flat even.

00:56:35.440 --> 00:56:38.690
So that's the result.

00:56:38.690 --> 00:56:39.940
What does this suggest?

00:56:41.980 --> 00:56:43.520
What happened to the
evolutionary psychology?

00:56:48.150 --> 00:56:49.600
It disappeared just by
having the women

00:56:49.600 --> 00:56:50.350
rotate around the room.

00:56:50.350 --> 00:56:52.630
It suggests, and we don't know
this with certainty.

00:56:52.630 --> 00:56:54.680
But people are following this up
who are interested in this.

00:56:54.680 --> 00:56:57.770
It suggests that there's
something about getting up and

00:56:57.770 --> 00:57:02.240
approaching that person, your
body going here I come, I'm

00:57:02.240 --> 00:57:06.230
not sitting in my chair hanging
out, it's like here I

00:57:06.230 --> 00:57:10.500
come, that makes a person
energized, feel more romantic,

00:57:10.500 --> 00:57:12.610
feel more chemistry is
happening, and more likely to

00:57:12.610 --> 00:57:13.340
ask on a date.

00:57:13.340 --> 00:57:14.740
And it doesn't matter
whether you're a man

00:57:14.740 --> 00:57:16.820
or a woman at all.

00:57:16.820 --> 00:57:20.060
It's the getting up and that
physical approach.

00:57:20.060 --> 00:57:20.880
You're more invested.

00:57:20.880 --> 00:57:21.530
You're more out there.

00:57:21.530 --> 00:57:24.160
Who knows what it is, completely
eliminates what

00:57:24.160 --> 00:57:27.220
everybody had said is an
ancient, inevitable,

00:57:27.220 --> 00:57:29.670
evolutionary difference
between men and women.

00:57:29.670 --> 00:57:31.610
And this isn't to say there
might not be some of those

00:57:31.610 --> 00:57:32.320
streaks in us.

00:57:32.320 --> 00:57:33.340
Who knows.

00:57:33.340 --> 00:57:34.690
But speed dating is
not showing that.

00:57:34.690 --> 00:57:36.325
All you got to do is have
the women rotate.

00:57:36.325 --> 00:57:38.740
And you completely eliminate
what's thought to be some

00:57:38.740 --> 00:57:42.620
hard-wired biological difference
on this dimension.

00:57:42.620 --> 00:57:45.190
Now, talking about that, when
we do experiments like this

00:57:45.190 --> 00:57:49.640
that look at sort of fun things
like dating around a

00:57:49.640 --> 00:57:52.110
thing or age difference between
a five-year-old and a

00:57:52.110 --> 00:57:54.810
20-year-old or a 20-year-old and
a 80-year-old, cultures,

00:57:54.810 --> 00:57:57.670
there's lots of experiments
that compare say Western

00:57:57.670 --> 00:58:01.510
