cultures, we'll talk about

00:58:01.510 --> 00:58:04.110
that later in the course in
terms of behaviors, genes,

00:58:04.110 --> 00:58:07.720
whether you have one gene or
another, all those things, are

00:58:07.720 --> 00:58:08.970
those independent variables?

00:58:13.960 --> 00:58:14.850
No.

00:58:14.850 --> 00:58:18.850
We can't assign you randomly to
be a man or a woman, young

00:58:18.850 --> 00:58:22.040
or old, to come from the United
States or Japan or

00:58:22.040 --> 00:58:25.370
China, or to have this
gene or that gene.

00:58:25.370 --> 00:58:29.690
It's not that we couldn't do
stuff in some monstrous world

00:58:29.690 --> 00:58:30.630
but not ethically.

00:58:30.630 --> 00:58:32.970
And it's never going
to happen, right?

00:58:32.970 --> 00:58:35.590
So whenever you have science
that talks about differences

00:58:35.590 --> 00:58:39.560
between men and women or young
and old or cultures or genes,

00:58:39.560 --> 00:58:42.350
it's not really a completely
independent manipulation.

00:58:42.350 --> 00:58:44.340
We can't assign you randomly.

00:58:44.340 --> 00:58:46.510
And so it means everything in
the world about what it means

00:58:46.510 --> 00:58:49.120
to be a man or a woman, a
20-year-old or an 80-year old,

00:58:49.120 --> 00:58:51.730
come from this continent or that
continent, have this gene

00:58:51.730 --> 00:58:53.830
or that gene, those are not
things we can freely

00:58:53.830 --> 00:58:54.155
manipulate.

00:58:54.155 --> 00:58:56.920
And we have to be extra cautious
in interpreting those

00:58:56.920 --> 00:58:57.740
kinds of studies.

00:58:57.740 --> 00:59:00.200
Because we can't randomly assign
you to conditions.

00:59:00.200 --> 00:59:02.560
We just can't.

00:59:02.560 --> 00:59:06.230
And I didn't talk about the
